{"parse":{"title":"tutor","pageid":201740,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Tutor}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|tutour||archaic}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|tutour}}, from {{der|en|fro|tuteur}} ({{cog|fr|tuteur}}), from {{der|en|la|tūtor||a watcher, protector, guardian}}, from {{m|la|tueor|t=protect}}; see [[tuition]].\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{a|en|non-rhotic}}\n** {{a|en|RP}}\n*** {{IPA|en|/ˈtjuːtəː/|[ˈtʰjʊu̯tʰəː]|a=non-yod-coalescence}}\n**** {{audio|en|en-uk-tutor.ogg|a=UK}}\n*** {{IPA|en|/ˈt͡ʃuːtəː/|[ˈt͡ʃʰʊu̯tʰəː]|a=yod-coalescence}}\n* {{a|en|rhotic}}\n** {{a|en|GA|yod-dropping}}\n*** {{IPA|en|/ˈtutɚ/|[ˈtʰʊu̯tʰɚ]|~|[ˈtʰʊu̯tʰɹ̩]|a=non-t-flapping}}\n*** {{IPA|en|/ˈtuɾɚ/|[ˈtʰʊu̯ɾɚ]|~|[ˈtʰʊu̯ɾɹ̩]|a=t-flapping}}\n**** {{audio|en|en-us-tutor.ogg|a=US}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈt͡ʃuː.t̪oɾ/|[ˈt͡ʃuː.t̪oɾ]|~|[ˈt͡ʃuː.t̪or]|a=Philippines,yod-coalescence}}\n* {{rhymes|en|uːtə(ɹ)|s=2}}\n* {{hyph|en|tu|tor}}\n* {{hmp|en|tooter|Tudor}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# One who [[teaches]] another (usually called a ''[[student]]'', ''[[learner]]'', or ''[[tutee]]'') in a one-on-one or small-group interaction.\n#: {{ux|en|He passed the difficult class with help from his '''tutor'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|UK}} A [[university]] [[officer]] responsible for students in a particular [[hall]].\n# {{lb|en|UK}} A [[homeroom]].\n# {{lb|en|obsolete|or|Quebec|_|law}} One who has the charge of a child or pupil and his estate; a [[guardian]].\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{sense|one who teaches}} {{l|en|preceptor}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en\n|e-tutor\n|tutee\n|tutorage\n|tutorship\n|tutrix\n}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n{{col|en\n|intuition\n|tuition\n|tutelage\n|tutelar\n|tutelary\n|tutorial\n}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|one who teaches another}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|домашен учител|m}}, {{t+|bg|възпитател|m}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|tutor|m}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{qualifier|private teacher}} {{t|cmn|私人教師|tr=sīrén jiàoshī}}, {{qualifier|teacher who goes to student's home}} {{t+|cmn|家庭教師|tr=jiātíng jiàoshī}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|hjælpelærer|c}}, {{t|da|privatlærer|c}}, {{t|da|lektiehjælper|c}}\n* Dutch: {{t|nl|studiebegeleider}}, {{t+|nl|mentor}}, {{t|nl|privé-leraar}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|tuutori}}, {{t|fi|tutori}}, {{t|fi|tuutor}}, {{t+|fi|tutor}}, {{q|lower education}} {{t|fi|tukioppilas}}, {{t+|fi|tukari}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|tuteur|m}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|titor|m}}, {{t+|gl|aio|m}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Lehrer}}, {{t+|de|Nachhilfelehrer|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|προγυμναστής|m}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|παιδαγωγός|m}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|מורה פרטי|m}}\n* Higaonon: {{t|mba|magtutudlo}}\n* Irish: {{t+|ga|oide|m}}, {{t|ga|teagascóir|m}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|istitutore|m}}, {{t|it|istitutrice|f}}, {{t+|it|precettore|m}}, {{t+|it|precettrice|f}}, {{t+|it|aio|m}}, {{t+|it|aia|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|家庭教師|tr=かていきょうしkatei kyoushi}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|튜터}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|praeceptor|m}}, {{t|la|praeceptrix|f}}, {{t|la|tutor|m}}, {{t|la|ēductor|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|воспи́тувач|m}}, {{t+|mk|у́чител|m}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|pouako}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t|nb|hjelpelærer|m}}, {{t|nb|gruppelærer|m}}, {{t|nb|privatlærer|m}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{t|pdt|Priewautliera|m}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|tutor|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|tutor|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|meditator|m}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|репети́тор|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|скр̑бнӣк|m}}, {{t|sh|скрбкиња|f}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|skȓbnīk|m}}, {{t|sh|skrbkinja|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|tutor|m}}, {{t|es|protutor|m}}, {{t|es|contutor|m}} {{q|disused}}, {{t+|es|acudiente|m|f}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|informator|c}}, {{t+|sv|lärare|c}}, {{t+|sv|guvernant|c}}, {{t+|sv|privatlärare|c}}\n* Thai: {{t|th|ครูพิเศษ}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|lala}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|репети́тор|m}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|gia sư}}\n* Welsh: {{t|cy|tiwtor|m}}, {{t|cy|tiwtores|f}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[instruct]] or [[teach]], especially an individual or small group.\n#: {{ux|en|To help pay her tuition, the college student began to '''tutor''' high school students in calculus and physics.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|archaic}} To treat with authority or sternness.\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|to instruct or teach, especially to an individual or small group}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|давам уроци}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|輔導|tr=fǔdǎo}}, {{t|cmn|个人辅导}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|tuutoroida}}, {{t|fi|tutoroida}}, {{t+|fi|avustaa}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|teagasc}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|insegnare}}, {{t+|it|istruire}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|tutelar}}, {{t+|pt|tutorar}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|medita}}\n* Russian: {{t|ru|дава́ть уро́ки}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|enseñar}}, {{t+|es|instruir}}, {{t|es|tutorizar}}, {{t+|es|tutelar}}, {{t+|es|tutorar}} {{qualifier|DEA}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|undervisa}}, {{t+|sv|handleda}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n=====Further reading=====\n* {{R:Online Etymology Dictionary}}\n* {{R:Webster 1913}}\n* {{R:Century 1911}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{ellipsis|en|alt=Demonic tutor}}, name of an early ''{{w|Magic: The Gathering}}'' card with this effect.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|en|trading card games}} A card that allows one to search one's deck for one or more other cards.\n#* {{quote-newsgroup|en|author=kc...@pcmagic.com|title=tutor ideas|newsgroup=rec.games.trading-cards.magic.misc|id=<35271e02.1847089@news.pcmagic.net>|url=https://groups.google.com/forum/message/raw?msg=rec.games.trading-cards.magic.misc/-8GGLKByBCM/B0mOLkrMzUUJ|date=1998-04-05|accessdate=2019-05-09|text=here are some '''tutor''' cards i thought would be interesting.}}\n<!-- https://groups.google.com/forum/#!search/tutor$20cards/rec.games.trading-cards.magic.rules/Any0hdhLFQc/YX1g8Ect9OUJ & https://groups.google.com/forum/#!search/tutor$20cards/rec.games.trading-cards.magic.misc/mSvuFwi_KC8/M0-a-oNofRoJ -->\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|trading card games}} To [[fetch]] a card from one's deck.\n#* {{quote-newsgroup|en|author=David Seiler|year=2002|title=Type I -- What do you think about Wishes and how do you plan to break them?|newsgroup=rec.games.trading-cards.magic.strategy\n|url=https://groups.google.com/g/rec.games.trading-cards.magic.strategy/c/XYRCkLrxEaU/m/dzIuUDQhrb8J\n|text=Any instant that you move to the board can *only* be '''tutored''' for with Cunning Wish.\n}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=orttu|Routt|Trout|trout}}\n\n{{C|en|Education|Magic: The Gathering|Occupations}}\n\n==Catalan==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|ca|la|tutor|tūtōrem}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{ca-IPA|[ó(r)]}}<!-- per GDLC; pronun not given in DCVB -->\n* {{audio|ca|LL-Q7026 (cat)-Marvives-tutor.wav|a=Barcelona}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{ca-IPA}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ca-noun|m|f=+}}\n\n# {{l|en|tutor}} {{gloss|teacher}}\n# [[guardian]] {{gloss|person responsible for another}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|ca|tutela}}\n* {{l|ca|tutoria}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:ca:DCVB}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:ca:IEC2}}\n\n==Chinese==\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{bor|yue|en|tutor}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n{{zh-pron\n|c=tiu1 taa2,tiu1 taa4\n|cat=n\n}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|zh|noun}}\n\n# {{lb|zh|Hong Kong Cantonese}} {{l|en|tutor}} {{gl|one who teaches}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom clipping of {{der|yue|en|tutorial|'''tutor'''ial}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n{{zh-pron\n|c=tiu6 to1\n|cat=n\n}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|zh|noun}}\n\n# {{lb|zh|Hong Kong Cantonese|university slang}} [[tutorial]]\n#: {{zh-co|上{soeng5} tu{iu6}tor{1}|to attend tutorial class|C}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:yue:ELHKC}}\n* {{cite-journal|zh|author=John Gibbons|title=Code-mixing and code choice : a Hong Kong case study|journal=Multilingual Matters|year=1987|page=56}}\n\n==Finnish==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{fi-p|tu(ː)tor}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fi-noun}}\n\n# {{alt form|fi|tuutori}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{fi-decl-paperi|tutor|a|i=0}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|fi\n|tutoroida\n}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fi:KTSK|accessdate=2023-07-03}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|fi|a=orttu|rutot|rutto|torut|turot}}\n\n==Indonesian==\n{{wp|id:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|id|en|tutor}}, from {{der|id|enm|tutour}}, from {{der|id|fro|tuteur}} ({{cog|fr|tuteur}}), from {{der|id|la|tūtor||a watcher, protector, guardian}}, {{m|la|tueor|t=protect}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{id-pr}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{id-noun|a}}\n\n# {{l|en|tutor}}\n## one who teaches another (usually called a student, learner, or tutee) in a one-on-one or small-group interaction.\n## a university officer responsible for students in a particular hall.\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|id|title=\n| tutor berkualifikasi| tutor berpengalaman| tutor bimbel| tutor keaksaraan| tutor pengampu| tutor privat| tutor sebaya\n|}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:KBBI Daring}}\n\n==Latin==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{la-IPA|tūtor}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{affix|la|tueor|-tor}}, via the old past participle {{m|la|tūtus}} (later replaced by {{m|la|tuitus}}).\n\n====Noun====\n{{la-noun|tūtor<3>|f=tūtrīx}}\n\n# [[watcher]], [[protector]], [[defender]]\n# [[guardian]] (of minors)\n# {{l|en|tutor}}\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{la-ndecl|tūtor<3>}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n{{col-top|2|desc}}\n* {{desc|ca|tutor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|en|tutor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fi|tuutori|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fr|tuteur|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|gl|titor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|it|tutore|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|pt|tutor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|es|tutor|bor=1}}\n{{col-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{affix|la|tueor|-tō}}, via the old past participle {{m|la|tūtus}} (later replaced by {{m|la|tuitus}}).\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alt|la|tūtō}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{la-verb|1+.p3inf|tūtor}}\n\n# to [[guard]], [[protect]], [[defend]]\n#: {{syn|la|prōtegō|dēfendō|vindicō|salvō|cū̆stōdiō|sospitō|praeservō|arceō|servō|tegō|adsum|tueor|sustineō|teneō|adimō|prohibeō|mūniō|ēripiō}}\n#: {{ant|la|immineō|īnstō|obiectō}}\n# to [[ward off]], [[avert]]\n\n=====Conjugation=====\n{{la-conj|1+.p3inf|tūtor}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n{{top2}}\n* Insular Romance:\n** {{desc|sc|tutare|qq=Bitti}}\n* Italo-Romance:\n** {{desc|it|tutare|qq=archaic}}\n* Northern Gallo-Romance:\n** {{desc|frp|tuar}}\n** {{desc|fro|tuer}} {{see desc}}\n* Southern Gallo-Romance:\n** {{desc|ca|tudar|qq=archaic, dialectal}}\n** {{desc|pro|tudar|tuar}}\n*** {{desc|oc|tuar}}\n* {{desc|la-vul|*extūtāre|alt=*adtūtāre, *distūtāre,*extūtāre|der=1}} {{see desc}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:FEW|13|vol_part=2|449|tutari}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:la:L&S}}\n* {{R:la:Elementary Lewis}}\n* {{R:la:du Cange}}\n* {{R:la:Peck}}\n* {{R:Smith's Antiquities}}\n\n==Polish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|pl|en|tutor}}, from {{der|pl|enm|tutour}}, from {{der|pl|fro|tuteur}}, from {{der|pl|la|tūtor}}, from {{m|la|tueor}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pl-pr|a=LL-Q809 (pol)-Poemat-tutor.wav}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pl-noun|m-pr}}\n\n# {{l|en|tutor}} {{gl|university officer responsible for students in a particular hall}}\n# {{lb|pl|archaic}} {{l|en|tutor}} {{gl|one who teaches another in a one-on-one or small-group interaction}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{pl-decl-noun-m-pr}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|pl|title=adjective|tutorski}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pl:PWN}}\n\n{{C|pl|Education|Male people|Occupations}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{lbor|pt|la|tutor|tūtōrem}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pt-IPA}}\n* {{rhymes|pt|oɾ|q1=Portugal, São Paulo|oʁ|q2=Brazil|s=2}}\n* {{hyph|pt|tu|tor}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pt-noun|m|f=+}}\n\n# {{l|en|tutor}} {{gloss|one who teaches in a one-on-one or small-group interaction}}\n# {{lb|pt|legal}} [[guardian]] {{gloss|person legally responsible for a minor or incompetent person}}\n# {{lb|pt|neologism}} [[pet]] [[owner]]\n#: {{syn|pt|dono}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|pt|tutoria|tutorar|tutorear|tutorial}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|tet|tutór|bor=1}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pt:Aulete}}\n* {{R:pt:Infopédia}}\n* {{R:pt:Priberam}}\n\n==Serbo-Croatian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|sh|la|tutor}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|sh|/tûːtor/}}\n* {{hyphenation|sh|tu|tor}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sh-noun|tȗtor|m-an}}\n\n# {{l|en|tutor}}\n# [[guardian]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{sh-decl-noun\n|tutor|tutori\n|tutora|tutora\n|tutoru|tutorima\n|tutora|tutore\n|tutore|tutori\n|tutoru|tutorima\n|tutorom|tutorima\n}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:sh:HJP|f19iWRB5}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|es|la|tutor|tutorem}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{es-noun|m|f=+}}\n\n# [[guardian]] {{gloss|person responsible for another}}\n# {{l|en|tutor}} {{gloss|teacher}}\n# {{lb|es|Spain}} {{q|US}} [[homeroom]] [[teacher]], {{q|UK}} [[form]] [[teacher]]\n# {{lb|es|horticulture}} [[trellis]]\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|es|tutela|tutoría}}\n\n====Further reading====\n* {{R:es:DRAE}}\n\n{{C|es|Education}}\n\n==Swedish==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|sv|noun form}}\n\n# {{noun form of|sv|tuta||indef|p}}"}}